    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long dresses with butterfly sleeves, considered part of the national costume for women in the Philippines, and made of jusi or polyester organza. Unlike the barong Tagalog worn by males, terno are worn mostly during special occasions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
